      <h1>Artist Profile: Logic Moon (Tobias Lorsbach)</h1>

      <h2>Biographical Information</h2>

      <p>
        Tobias <em>"Logic Moon"</em> Lorsbach comes from Mainz, Germany. He began
        his musical career as a DJ and was active in the minimal techno scene in
        the early 2000s. At the same time, he played guitar in a death metal band
        until he increasingly turned to ambient music. During a <strong
          >field recording trip</strong
        >, the idea arose to combine ambient drone elements with his recordings
        – this resulted in his debut album <em>Herbst11</em> as Logic Moon in 2013.
        His compositions often begin with a guitar sketch, followed by synthesizers
        and other layers. This <strong>cross-genre background</strong> (techno, metal,
        ambient) shapes his stylistic approach: The press describes that Tobias as
        Logic Moon makes "guitar-oriented ambient and drone music" and his music
        is often perceived as "lively" and as a balance between classical accessibility
        and experimental discovery.
      </p>

