            >The Unavoidable Death of Loneliness</em
          > (2022, Ambientologist) and <em>The Quiet Companion</em> (2023, Shimmering
          Moods). Both albums show the close musical partnership of the two composers.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Henrik Meierkord</strong> – The Swedish cellist appeared on the
          mini albums <em>Ewiger Wald</em> and <em>Ewiger Wald Addendum</em> (2024).
          Logic Moon mixes his electronic drones with Meierkord's cello into neoclassical
          ambient studies here.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Julia Gjertsen</strong> – The singer is a guest on <em
            >The Quiet Companion</em
          > (track "Together But Apart"), which gives the album an additional emotional
          note.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Scarless Arms (Tyve Oben)</strong> – With this producer, Logic
          Moon shared the <em>Moon Scars</em> EP in 2023, a six-track collaboration
          in cinematic ambient style.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Labels</strong> – In addition to the already mentioned labels Ambientologist
          and Shimmering Moods, he released on Archipel (D DR), Archives (GB), DE_ST_REC,
          Dronarivm (D), Whitelabrecs (JP) and his own label Logic Moon Records or
          spontanMusik. This collaboration with renowned ambient labels has given
          him international visibility in the scene.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Reviews and Criticism</h2>

      <p>
        Logic Moon received positive response in the trade press and ambient
        blogs. For example, Ambientblog praises the cinematic character of his
        work, such as the album <em>The Unavoidable Death of Loneliness</em>,
        which "combines post-classical arrangements and ambient soundscapes into
        adventurous, cinematic compositions." International websites also
        highlight how well Logic Moon's style complements his partners.
        Headphone Commute describes <em>The Quiet Companion</em> as a collection
        of "gentle, neoclassical pieces with piano, synthesizer pads and strings"
        that harmoniously grow together despite spatial distance. In interviews and
        features, it is often emphasized that Tobias Lorsbach's experience from techno
        and metal as well as his use of guitars and field recordings give his ambient
        music an organic depth. Listeners appreciate the emotional access and the
        multi-layered atmosphere of his albums, as fan reviews and blog features
        repeatedly confirm. Overall, Logic Moon is considered a seasoned producer
        with consistently high quality: His releases are usually perceived as <strong
          >"expressive"</strong
        > and <strong>"finely balanced"</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>Influence and Significance</h2>

      <p>
        Logic Moon is among the active players in the contemporary ambient and
        experimental scene. Through numerous releases on international labels
        and his collaborations, he contributes to the network of European
        ambient artists. With over 40 releases since 2012, he has established a
        firm place in the scene. His style – the combination of electronic
        ambient music with neoclassical and acoustic elements – inspires other
        artists to explore similar cross-genre soundscapes. He also engages as a
        curator (e.g. of ambient playlists on streaming services) and thus
        shapes the listening habits of the community. In sum, Logic Moon is
        considered an <strong
          >important representative of the German ambient movement</strong
        >, whose works are regularly presented through specialized channels.
      </p>
